2007-11-04 04:04  Rocky Bernstein

	* trunk/Rakefile, rdebug, trunk/cli/ruby-debug.rb,
	  trunk/cli/ruby-debug/commands/settings.rb,
	  trunk/cli/ruby-debug/commands/show.rb,
	  trunk/cli/ruby-debug/processor.rb, trunk/emacs/rdebug-extra.el,
	  trunk/emacs/rdebug-test.el, trunk/emacs/rdebug.el: Debugger
	  "annotation" mode. This is used for example in GNU Emacs to
	  track the status of breakpoints, stack and local variables. But
	  it can
	  be used by other front-ends as well. The command-line option is
	  --annotate (-A) and there are set/show commands.
	  
	  Add emacs files to the package now. More complete Emacs code.

